$\begin{align}
p\,\times\, \blueD{?}&=c \\\\
\blueD{?}&=\dfrac{c}{p} \\\\
&=\blueD{\dfrac{7}{3}}
\end{align}$

The constant of proportionality is $\blueD{\dfrac{7}{3}}$.  This means we can multiply $\blueD{\dfrac{7}{3}}$ by the number of hours to get the total cost.

$\begin{align}
m\,\times\, \blueD{?}&=p \\\\
\blueD{?}&=\dfrac{p}{m} \\\\
&=\blueD{\dfrac{3}{8}}
\end{align}$

The constant of proportionality is $\blueD{\dfrac{3}{8}}$.  This means we can multiply $\blueD{\dfrac{3}{8}}$ by the number of minutes to get the number of pages.
